Quote:  That your memorialists believe that the Awaroa river might easily be rendered an excellent means of transit, and that a canal or tramroad might at a comparatively small expense be constructed from some point on that river to the Waiuku creek, by means whereof the communication between the town of Auckland and the before named Waikato district might be rendered complete.
